# Custom Cursor

## What It Is
A custom cursor that replaces the default browser cursor.
Two layered circles that follow the mouse.

## Two Elements
1. **Dot** — small 8px circle, follows mouse instantly
2. **Ring** — larger 32px circle, follows with spring lag

## Behavior

### Move
- Dot: follows cursor position instantly
- Ring: follows with spring physics — stiffness 150, damping 15
- Both use framer-motion useMotionValue + useSpring

### Hover (on any button, link, or [data-cursor="pointer"])
- Ring: scales up to 1.5x
- Ring: background fills with white at 10% opacity
- Dot: scales down to 0.5x
- Smooth transition

### Click
- Both elements: quick scale down to 0.8x then back
- Duration: 0.1s

## Style

### Dot
- 8px x 8px
- border-radius 50%
- background: var(--text-primary)
- position fixed
- pointer-events none
- z-index 9998
- transform: translate(-50%, -50%)

### Ring
- 32px x 32px
- border-radius 50%
- border: 1.5px solid var(--text-primary)
- background: transparent
- position fixed
- pointer-events none
- z-index 9998
- transform: translate(-50%, -50%)

## Rules
- "use client" required
- Hide default cursor on body: cursor none
- Only render on desktop — hide on touch devices
- Add to layout.tsx inside ThemeProvider alongside ScrollProgressBar
- pointer-events: none on both elements so they never block clicks